{"title":"$:/plugins/rimir/theme","description":"Shared visual theme for rimir plugins","name":"theme","author":"rimir","version":"0.1.7","core-version":">=5.3.0","source":"https://github.com/rimir-cc/tw-theme","plugin-type":"plugin","list":"readme documentation settings changelog license","soft-dependents":"$:/plugins/rimir/doc-template","dependents":"","type":"application/json","text":"{\"tiddlers\":{\"/home/runner/work/tw-plugin-library/tw-plugin-library/wiki/plugins/rimir/theme/.gitattributes\":{\"title\":\"/home/runner/work/tw-plugin-library/tw-plugin-library/wiki/plugins/rimir/theme/.gitattributes\",\"text\":\"* text=auto eol=lf\\n\",\"type\":\"text/plain\"},\"$:/plugins/rimir/theme/license\":{\"title\":\"$:/plugins/rimir/theme/license\",\"text\":\"MIT License\\n\\nCopyright (c) since 2026 rimir-cc (https://github.com/rimir-cc)\\n\\nPermission is hereby granted, free of charge, to any person obtaining a copy\\nof this software and associated documentation files (the \\\"Software\\\"), to deal\\nin the Software without restriction, including without limitation the rights\\nto use, copy, modify, merge, publish, distribute, sublicense, and/or sell\\ncopies of the Software, and to permit persons to whom the Software is\\nfurnished to do so, subject to the following conditions:\\n\\nThe above copyright notice and this permission notice shall be included in all\\ncopies or substantial portions of the Software.\\n\\nTHE SOFTWARE IS PROVIDED \\\"AS IS\\\", WITHOUT WARRANTY OF ANY KIND, EXPRESS OR\\nIMPLIED, INCLUDING BUT NOT LIMITED TO THE WARRANTIES OF MERCHANTABILITY,\\nFITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE AND NONINFRINGEMENT. IN NO EVENT SHALL THE\\nAUTHORS OR COPYRIGHT HOLDERS BE LIABLE FOR ANY CLAIM, DAMAGES OR OTHER\\nLIABILITY, WHETHER IN AN ACTION OF CONTRACT, TORT OR OTHERWISE, ARISING FROM,\\nOUT OF OR IN CONNECTION WITH THE SOFTWARE OR THE USE OR OTHER DEALINGS IN THE\\nSOFTWARE.\\n\",\"type\":\"text/x-markdown\"},\"/home/runner/work/tw-plugin-library/tw-plugin-library/wiki/plugins/rimir/theme/README.md\":{\"title\":\"/home/runner/work/tw-plugin-library/tw-plugin-library/wiki/plugins/rimir/theme/README.md\",\"text\":\"# theme\\n\\n> Shared visual theme for rimir plugins\\n\\nShared visual CSS classes (prefix `rr-`) used across all rimir plugins. Provides consistent styling for tabs, panels, tables, callouts, notices, badges, forms, status messages, and the settings hub layout.\\n\\n## Key features\\n\\n* **Tabs** -- `rr-tabs`, `rr-tab`, `rr-tab-active` for horizontal tab bars\\n* **Callouts** -- four types (info, warning, tip, danger) via reusable template\\n* **Notices** -- alert banners (warning, info, danger, success)\\n* **Badges** -- circular and rectangular pill badges\\n* **Settings hub layout** -- sidebar + content panel classes for core-hook\\n* **Utilities** -- muted, mono, nowrap, small helper classes\\n\\n## Prerequisites\\n\\nNo external prerequisites.\\n\\n## Quick start\\n\\nInstall plugin. Use `rr-` prefixed CSS classes in your tiddlers. For callouts:\\n\\n```html\\n<$transclude $tiddler=\\\"$:/plugins/rimir/theme/callout\\\" type=\\\"info\\\">\\n<$fill $name=\\\"body\\\">Your message</$fill>\\n</$transclude>\\n```\\n\\n## Class reference\\n\\n### Tabs\\n\\n| Class | Purpose |\\n|-------|---------|\\n| `rr-tabs` | Flex container for tab bar |\\n| `rr-tab` | Individual tab button |\\n| `rr-tab-active` | Active tab (add alongside `rr-tab`) |\\n\\n```html\\n<div class=\\\"rr-tabs\\\">\\n  <$button class=\\\"rr-tab rr-tab-active\\\">Tab 1</$button>\\n  <$button class=\\\"rr-tab\\\">Tab 2</$button>\\n</div>\\n```\\n\\n### Panels\\n\\n| Class | Purpose |\\n|-------|---------|\\n| `rr-panel` | Bordered container with background |\\n| `rr-panel-body` | Padded inner content area |\\n\\n### Tables\\n\\n| Class | Purpose |\\n|-------|---------|\\n| `rr-table` | Full-width collapsed table |\\n| `rr-row-error` | Red background row (on `<tr>`) |\\n| `rr-row-warn` | Yellow background row (on `<tr>`) |\\n\\n### Callouts\\n\\nUse the template `$:/plugins/rimir/theme/callout` with parameters `type` (`info`/`warning`/`tip`/`danger`) and optional `label`.\\n\\n| Class | Purpose |\\n|-------|---------|\\n| `rr-callout` | Base callout box |\\n| `rr-callout-info` | Blue left border |\\n| `rr-callout-warning` | Amber left border |\\n| `rr-callout-tip` | Green left border |\\n| `rr-callout-danger` | Red left border |\\n| `rr-callout-label` | Bold uppercase label |\\n\\n### Notices\\n\\nUse the template `$:/plugins/rimir/theme/notice` with parameter `type` (`warning`/`info`/`danger`/`success`).\\n\\n| Class | Purpose |\\n|-------|---------|\\n| `rr-notice` | Base notice banner |\\n| `rr-notice-warning` | Yellow background |\\n| `rr-notice-info` | Light blue background |\\n| `rr-notice-danger` | Light red background |\\n| `rr-notice-success` | Light green background |\\n\\n### Status Messages\\n\\n| Class | Purpose |\\n|-------|---------|\\n| `rr-status-loading` | Muted italic loading text |\\n| `rr-status-error` | Red alert box |\\n| `rr-status-success` | Green success box |\\n| `rr-status-info` | Muted info text |\\n\\n### Badges\\n\\n| Class | Purpose |\\n|-------|---------|\\n| `rr-badge-circle` | 16px round badge |\\n| `rr-badge-added` | Green circle (use with `rr-badge-circle`) |\\n| `rr-badge-removed` | Red circle (use with `rr-badge-circle`) |\\n| `rr-badge-rect` | Rectangular pill badge |\\n\\n### Forms\\n\\n| Class | Purpose |\\n|-------|---------|\\n| `rr-input-row` | Flex row with gap |\\n| `rr-input` | Styled text input |\\n\\n### Link Buttons\\n\\n| Class | Purpose |\\n|-------|---------|\\n| `rr-link-btn` | Primary-colored link-style button |\\n| `rr-link-btn-danger` | Alert-colored variant (add alongside `rr-link-btn`) |\\n\\n### Settings Hub\\n\\n| Class | Purpose |\\n|-------|---------|\\n| `rr-settings-hub` | Flex container for sidebar + content layout |\\n| `rr-settings-sidebar` | Left sidebar with plugin list |\\n| `rr-settings-plugin-item` | Sidebar button for each plugin |\\n| `rr-settings-plugin-active` | Active state highlight (accent border) |\\n| `rr-settings-plugin-name` | Plugin name text (truncated) |\\n| `rr-settings-plugin-version` | Version badge |\\n| `rr-settings-content` | Right content area |\\n| `rr-settings-header` | Plugin header with icon + name + description |\\n| `rr-settings-header-name` | Plugin name in header |\\n| `rr-settings-header-desc` | Plugin description in header |\\n| `rr-settings-info-card` | Dashed info card for plugins without settings |\\n\\n### Utilities\\n\\n| Class | Purpose |\\n|-------|---------|\\n| `rr-muted` | Muted foreground color |\\n| `rr-mono` | Monospace font |\\n| `rr-nowrap` | No text wrapping |\\n| `rr-small` | 0.85em font size |\\n\\n## Plugin Library\\n\\nInstall from the [rimir plugin library](https://rimir-cc.github.io/tw-plugin-library/) via *Control Panel â†’ Plugins â†’ Get more plugins*.\\n\\n## Demo\\n\\nTry this plugin in the [live demo wiki](https://rimir-cc.github.io/tw-demo/).\\n\\n## License\\n\\nMIT -- see [LICENSE.md](LICENSE.md)\\n\",\"type\":\"text/x-markdown\"},\"$:/plugins/rimir/theme/callout\":{\"title\":\"$:/plugins/rimir/theme/callout\",\"created\":\"20260305110732194\",\"modified\":\"20260305110732194\",\"type\":\"text/vnd.tiddlywiki\",\"text\":\"\\\\parameters (type:\\\"info\\\", label:\\\"\\\")\\n\\n<$let\\n  calloutClass={{{ [[rr-callout rr-callout-]addsuffix<type>] }}}\\n  resolvedLabel={{{ [<label>!is[blank]] :else[<type>uppercase[]] }}}\\n>\\n<div class=<<calloutClass>>>\\n<div class=\\\"rr-callout-label\\\"><$text text=<<resolvedLabel>>/></div>\\n<$slot $name=\\\"body\\\">\\n//No callout content.//\\n</$slot>\\n</div>\\n</$let>\\n\"},\"$:/plugins/rimir/theme/changelog\":{\"title\":\"$:/plugins/rimir/theme/changelog\",\"created\":\"20260305110732194\",\"modified\":\"20260305110732194\",\"type\":\"text/vnd.tiddlywiki\",\"text\":\"! Changelog\\n\\n|!Version |!Date |!Changes |\\n|v0.1.7 |2026-04-30 |New reusable `rr-text-view-editable` template â€” wraps a block-mode transclude in an `$eventcatcher` whose `$dblclick` flips a caller-supplied `editState` to `\\\"yes\\\"`. Caller passes `editState` via `<$let>` (and optionally `viewTiddler`); falls back to surrounding `<$tiddler>`/currentTiddler context. Subtle `cursor:text` hint via new `.rr-text-view-editable` rule. Pairs with `rr-text-editor` so the same `editState` flips both directions (dblclick â†’ enter, Ctrl+Enter â†’ leave) |\\n|v0.1.6 |2026-04-29 |New reusable `rr-text-editor` template that wraps `<$edit-text>` with hidden EditorToolbar children so framed-engine keyboard shortcuts (bold, italic, headings, autolist if installed) bind in any consuming view. Includes a hidden Ctrl+Enter ''leave edit mode'' toolbar item gated by the caller's `editState` variable so it only binds inside this template, not in standard TW editors |\\n|v0.1.5 |2026-04-27 |Declare `doc-template` as soft-dependent in plugin.info |\\n|v0.1.4 |2026-03-15 |Add missing doc tiddlers (architecture, dev-workflow, examples, faq, reference, tw-internals) |\\n|v0.1.3 |2026-03-15 |Add name field to plugin.info |\\n|v0.1.2 |2026-03-15 |Add regression tests and CI test gate |\\n|v0.1.1 |2026-03-06 |Standardize plugin tabs: add documentation/changelog/license to list, replace license.tid with LICENSE.md.meta sidecar |\\n|v0.1.0 |2026 |Initial release |\\n\"},\"$:/plugins/rimir/theme/doc/architecture\":{\"title\":\"$:/plugins/rimir/theme/doc/architecture\",\"created\":\"20260315120000000\",\"modified\":\"20260315120000000\",\"rdt.order\":\"2\",\"rdt.plugin-key\":\"theme\",\"rdt.plugin-name\":\"theme\",\"rdt.plugin-subtitle\":\"Shared visual CSS classes for rimir plugins\",\"rdt.section\":\"Architecture\",\"type\":\"text/vnd.tiddlywiki\",\"text\":\"<$transclude $tiddler=\\\"$:/plugins/rimir/doc-template/templates/page\\\">\\n<$fill $name=\\\"body\\\">\\n\\n!! Single stylesheet\\n\\nAll CSS is defined in `styles.tid`, tagged `$:/tags/Stylesheet`. TiddlyWiki loads all stylesheet-tagged tiddlers at startup and injects them into the page. The `rr-` prefix namespaces all classes to avoid collisions with TW core or other plugins.\\n\\n!! Reusable templates\\n\\nTwo wikitext templates provide parameterized UI components:\\n\\n|!Template |!Tiddler |!Parameters |\\n|Callout |`$:/plugins/rimir/theme/callout` |`type` (info/warning/tip/danger), optional `label` |\\n|Notice |`$:/plugins/rimir/theme/notice` |`type` (warning/info/danger/success) |\\n\\nThese are consumed via `<$transclude $tiddler=\\\"...\\\" type=\\\"...\\\">` with `<$fill $name=\\\"body\\\">` for content injection.\\n\\n!! TW colour macros\\n\\nThe stylesheet uses TiddlyWiki's `<<colour ...>>` macros (e.g., `<<colour tiddler-border>>`, `<<colour page-background>>`, `<<colour muted-foreground>>`) to inherit the active palette's colors. This means rimir plugins automatically adapt to custom TW palettes.\\n\\n!! Design principles\\n\\n* ''Single source'' â€” one `styles.tid` file, no scattered CSS across plugins\\n* ''Prefix convention'' â€” all classes use `rr-` to avoid naming conflicts\\n* ''Palette-aware'' â€” uses TW colour macros, not hardcoded colors (except for semantic callout/notice borders)\\n* ''No JS'' â€” pure CSS + wikitext templates, no startup modules\\n\\n</$fill>\\n</$transclude>\\n\"},\"$:/plugins/rimir/theme/doc/dev-workflow\":{\"title\":\"$:/plugins/rimir/theme/doc/dev-workflow\",\"created\":\"20260315120000000\",\"modified\":\"20260315120000000\",\"rdt.order\":\"3\",\"rdt.plugin-key\":\"theme\",\"rdt.plugin-name\":\"theme\",\"rdt.plugin-subtitle\":\"Shared visual CSS classes for rimir plugins\",\"rdt.section\":\"Dev Workflow\",\"type\":\"text/vnd.tiddlywiki\",\"text\":\"<$transclude $tiddler=\\\"$:/plugins/rimir/doc-template/templates/page\\\">\\n<$fill $name=\\\"body\\\">\\n\\n!! Plugin files\\n\\n|!File |!Role |\\n|`styles.tid` |All CSS definitions â€” tagged `$:/tags/Stylesheet` |\\n|`callout.tid` |Reusable callout box template (info/warning/tip/danger) |\\n|`notice.tid` |Reusable notice banner template (warning/info/danger/success) |\\n|`settings.tid` |Settings panel (minimal â€” no configurable settings) |\\n|`readme.tid` |Plugin readme with full class reference |\\n|`icon.tid` |SVG icon |\\n|`plugin.info` |Plugin metadata |\\n\\n!! Restart rules\\n\\n|!Change |!Restart needed? |\\n|`styles.tid` |Yes â€” plugin shadow tiddler, requires server restart |\\n|`callout.tid` / `notice.tid` |Yes â€” plugin shadow tiddlers |\\n|Any doc/readme `.tid` |Yes â€” plugin shadow tiddlers |\\n\\n<$transclude $tiddler=\\\"$:/plugins/rimir/doc-template/templates/callout\\\" type=\\\"info\\\">\\n<$fill $name=\\\"body\\\">\\nTheme has no JS modules â€” all files are wikitext/CSS shadow tiddlers. \\\"Restart\\\" means restarting the TiddlyWiki server so updated shadow tiddlers are loaded.\\n</$fill>\\n</$transclude>\\n\\n!! Adding new classes\\n\\nWhen adding a new `rr-` class:\\n\\n# Add the CSS rule to `styles.tid` in the appropriate section (tabs, panels, tables, etc.)\\n# Document the class in `readme.tid` under the relevant subsection\\n# If the class is part of a reusable pattern (like callouts), consider creating a wikitext template\\n\\n!! Consuming plugins\\n\\nOther rimir plugins import theme classes by simply using `class=\\\"rr-...\\\"` in their wikitext or by transclusing the callout/notice templates. No import statement or dependency declaration is needed beyond listing theme in `tiddlywiki.info`.\\n\\n</$fill>\\n</$transclude>\\n\"},\"$:/plugins/rimir/theme/doc/examples\":{\"title\":\"$:/plugins/rimir/theme/doc/examples\",\"created\":\"20260315120000000\",\"modified\":\"20260315120000000\",\"rdt.order\":\"4\",\"rdt.plugin-key\":\"theme\",\"rdt.plugin-name\":\"theme\",\"rdt.plugin-subtitle\":\"Shared visual CSS classes for rimir plugins\",\"rdt.section\":\"Examples\",\"type\":\"text/vnd.tiddlywiki\",\"text\":\"<$transclude $tiddler=\\\"$:/plugins/rimir/doc-template/templates/page\\\">\\n<$fill $name=\\\"body\\\">\\n\\n!! Callout boxes\\n\\n```\\n<$transclude $tiddler=\\\"$:/plugins/rimir/theme/callout\\\" type=\\\"info\\\">\\n<$fill $name=\\\"body\\\">This is an informational callout.</$fill>\\n</$transclude>\\n\\n<$transclude $tiddler=\\\"$:/plugins/rimir/theme/callout\\\" type=\\\"warning\\\" label=\\\"Caution\\\">\\n<$fill $name=\\\"body\\\">This callout has a custom label.</$fill>\\n</$transclude>\\n\\n<$transclude $tiddler=\\\"$:/plugins/rimir/theme/callout\\\" type=\\\"danger\\\">\\n<$fill $name=\\\"body\\\">Danger callout for critical warnings.</$fill>\\n</$transclude>\\n\\n<$transclude $tiddler=\\\"$:/plugins/rimir/theme/callout\\\" type=\\\"tip\\\">\\n<$fill $name=\\\"body\\\">A helpful tip for the reader.</$fill>\\n</$transclude>\\n```\\n\\n!! Tab bar\\n\\n```\\n<div class=\\\"rr-tabs\\\">\\n  <$button class=\\\"rr-tab rr-tab-active\\\" set=\\\"$:/state/demo-tab\\\" setTo=\\\"one\\\">Tab 1</$button>\\n  <$button class=\\\"rr-tab\\\" set=\\\"$:/state/demo-tab\\\" setTo=\\\"two\\\">Tab 2</$button>\\n</div>\\n<$reveal state=\\\"$:/state/demo-tab\\\" type=\\\"match\\\" text=\\\"one\\\" default=\\\"one\\\">\\nContent for tab 1.\\n</$reveal>\\n<$reveal state=\\\"$:/state/demo-tab\\\" type=\\\"match\\\" text=\\\"two\\\">\\nContent for tab 2.\\n</$reveal>\\n```\\n\\n!! Notice banner\\n\\n```\\n<$transclude $tiddler=\\\"$:/plugins/rimir/theme/notice\\\" type=\\\"warning\\\">\\n<$fill $name=\\\"body\\\">This feature is experimental.</$fill>\\n</$transclude>\\n```\\n\\n</$fill>\\n</$transclude>\\n\"},\"$:/plugins/rimir/theme/doc/faq\":{\"title\":\"$:/plugins/rimir/theme/doc/faq\",\"created\":\"20260315120000000\",\"modified\":\"20260315120000000\",\"rdt.order\":\"5\",\"rdt.plugin-key\":\"theme\",\"rdt.plugin-name\":\"theme\",\"rdt.plugin-subtitle\":\"Shared visual CSS classes for rimir plugins\",\"rdt.section\":\"FAQ\",\"type\":\"text/vnd.tiddlywiki\",\"text\":\"<$transclude $tiddler=\\\"$:/plugins/rimir/doc-template/templates/page\\\">\\n<$fill $name=\\\"body\\\">\\n\\n!! Q: Do I need the theme plugin if I only use one rimir plugin?\\n\\nYes, if that plugin uses `rr-` CSS classes (most do). Without theme, the UI will render but without proper styling â€” no borders, no spacing, no callout colors. Check the plugin's dependencies to confirm.\\n\\n!! Q: Will theme conflict with my custom TW palette?\\n\\nNo. Theme uses TiddlyWiki's `<<colour ...>>` macros for most colors (borders, backgrounds, muted text), so it inherits your active palette automatically. Only semantic colors (callout borders, notice backgrounds) use hardcoded values.\\n\\n!! Q: How do I override a specific `rr-` class?\\n\\nCreate a tiddler tagged `$:/tags/Stylesheet` with higher specificity or an `!important` rule. Since TW loads stylesheet tiddlers in alphabetical order by title, you can also use a title that sorts after the theme's `styles.tid` to ensure your overrides load later.\\n\\n</$fill>\\n</$transclude>\\n\"},\"$:/plugins/rimir/theme/doc/overview\":{\"title\":\"$:/plugins/rimir/theme/doc/overview\",\"created\":\"20260305110732195\",\"modified\":\"20260305110732195\",\"rdt.hub-category\":\"infrastructure\",\"rdt.hub-category-name\":\"Infrastructure\",\"rdt.hub-order\":\"2\",\"rdt.order\":\"1\",\"rdt.plugin-key\":\"theme\",\"rdt.plugin-name\":\"theme\",\"rdt.plugin-subtitle\":\"Shared visual CSS classes for rimir plugins\",\"rdt.section\":\"Overview\",\"type\":\"text/vnd.tiddlywiki\",\"text\":\"<$transclude $tiddler=\\\"$:/plugins/rimir/doc-template/templates/page\\\">\\n<$fill $name=\\\"body\\\">\\n\\n!! What it does\\n\\nTheme provides a centralised set of CSS classes (prefix `rr-`) used across all rimir plugins. It eliminates duplicate styling by offering consistent patterns for tabs, panels, tables, callouts, notices, badges, forms, and the settings hub layout.\\n\\n!! Features\\n\\n* ''Tabs'' â€” `rr-tabs`, `rr-tab`, `rr-tab-active` for horizontal tab bars\\n* ''Panels'' â€” bordered containers with padded content area\\n* ''Tables'' â€” full-width collapsed tables with error/warning row styles\\n* ''Callouts'' â€” four types (info, warning, tip, danger) via reusable template\\n* ''Notices'' â€” alert banners (warning, info, danger, success)\\n* ''Badges'' â€” circular and rectangular pill badges\\n* ''Forms'' â€” styled inputs and flex row layout\\n* ''Settings hub'' â€” sidebar + content layout for the core-hook settings panel\\n* ''Utilities'' â€” muted, mono, nowrap, small helper classes\\n\\n!! Plugin files\\n\\n|!File |!Role |\\n|`styles.tid` |All CSS definitions (`rr-*` prefix) |\\n|`callout.tid` |Reusable callout box template |\\n|`notice.tid` |Reusable notice banner template |\\n\\n</$fill>\\n</$transclude>\\n\"},\"$:/plugins/rimir/theme/doc/reference\":{\"title\":\"$:/plugins/rimir/theme/doc/reference\",\"created\":\"20260315120000000\",\"modified\":\"20260315120000000\",\"rdt.order\":\"6\",\"rdt.plugin-key\":\"theme\",\"rdt.plugin-name\":\"theme\",\"rdt.plugin-subtitle\":\"Shared visual CSS classes for rimir plugins\",\"rdt.section\":\"Reference\",\"type\":\"text/vnd.tiddlywiki\",\"text\":\"<$transclude $tiddler=\\\"$:/plugins/rimir/doc-template/templates/page\\\">\\n<$fill $name=\\\"body\\\">\\n\\n!! Tabs\\n\\n|!Class |!Purpose |\\n|`rr-tabs` |Flex container for tab bar |\\n|`rr-tab` |Individual tab button |\\n|`rr-tab-active` |Active tab highlight (add alongside `rr-tab`) |\\n\\n!! Panels\\n\\n|!Class |!Purpose |\\n|`rr-panel` |Bordered container with background |\\n|`rr-panel-body` |Padded inner content area |\\n\\n!! Tables\\n\\n|!Class |!Purpose |\\n|`rr-table` |Full-width collapsed table |\\n|`rr-row-error` |Red background row |\\n|`rr-row-warn` |Yellow background row |\\n\\n!! Callouts\\n\\nTemplate: `$:/plugins/rimir/theme/callout`\\n\\n|!Parameter |!Values |!Description |\\n|`type` |`info`, `warning`, `tip`, `danger` |Callout style (border color + icon) |\\n|`label` |(optional) |Custom bold uppercase label |\\n\\n|!Class |!Purpose |\\n|`rr-callout` |Base callout box |\\n|`rr-callout-info` |Blue left border |\\n|`rr-callout-warning` |Amber left border |\\n|`rr-callout-tip` |Green left border |\\n|`rr-callout-danger` |Red left border |\\n|`rr-callout-label` |Bold uppercase label |\\n\\n!! Notices\\n\\nTemplate: `$:/plugins/rimir/theme/notice`\\n\\n|!Parameter |!Values |!Description |\\n|`type` |`warning`, `info`, `danger`, `success` |Notice style |\\n\\n|!Class |!Purpose |\\n|`rr-notice` |Base notice banner |\\n|`rr-notice-warning` |Yellow background |\\n|`rr-notice-info` |Light blue background |\\n|`rr-notice-danger` |Light red background |\\n|`rr-notice-success` |Light green background |\\n\\n!! Status messages\\n\\n|!Class |!Purpose |\\n|`rr-status-loading` |Muted italic loading text |\\n|`rr-status-error` |Red alert box |\\n|`rr-status-success` |Green success box |\\n|`rr-status-info` |Muted info text |\\n\\n!! Badges\\n\\n|!Class |!Purpose |\\n|`rr-badge-circle` |16px round badge |\\n|`rr-badge-added` |Green circle (use with `rr-badge-circle`) |\\n|`rr-badge-removed` |Red circle (use with `rr-badge-circle`) |\\n|`rr-badge-rect` |Rectangular pill badge |\\n\\n!! Forms\\n\\n|!Class |!Purpose |\\n|`rr-input-row` |Flex row with gap |\\n|`rr-input` |Styled text input |\\n\\n!! Link buttons\\n\\n|!Class |!Purpose |\\n|`rr-link-btn` |Primary-colored link-style button |\\n|`rr-link-btn-danger` |Alert-colored variant (add alongside `rr-link-btn`) |\\n\\n!! Settings hub\\n\\n|!Class |!Purpose |\\n|`rr-settings-hub` |Flex container (sidebar + content) |\\n|`rr-settings-sidebar` |Left sidebar with plugin list |\\n|`rr-settings-plugin-item` |Sidebar button per plugin |\\n|`rr-settings-plugin-active` |Active state highlight |\\n|`rr-settings-plugin-name` |Plugin name text (truncated) |\\n|`rr-settings-plugin-version` |Version badge |\\n|`rr-settings-content` |Right content area |\\n|`rr-settings-header` |Plugin header (icon + name + desc) |\\n|`rr-settings-info-card` |Dashed fallback card |\\n\\n!! Text Editor\\n\\nTemplate: `$:/plugins/rimir/theme/rr-text-editor`\\n\\nWraps `<$edit-text>` with EditorToolbar children so the framed editor engine binds keyboard shortcuts (bold, italic, headings, autolist if `sq/editor-autolist` is installed). Adds a hidden ''leave edit mode'' toolbar item bound to Ctrl+Enter that clears the caller's edit-state tiddler.\\n\\n|!Variable (via `<$let>`) |!Description |\\n|`editTiddler` |Title of the tiddler whose `text` field is being edited |\\n|`editState` |State tiddler that gates edit mode (cleared on Ctrl+Enter) |\\n|`wrapClass` |CSS class for the outer wrapper div (consumer-supplied, controls width/height) |\\n\\n```\\n<$let editTiddler=<<myNote>> editState=\\\"$:/state/my-edit\\\" wrapClass=\\\"my-editor\\\">\\n<$transclude $tiddler=\\\"$:/plugins/rimir/theme/rr-text-editor\\\"/>\\n</$let>\\n```\\n\\nThe toolbar is hidden via `.rr-text-editor-host > .tc-editor-toolbar { display: none }` (added in this plugin). Shortcuts still fire because TW core's `framed.js` engine looks them up via `querySelectorAll(\\\"[data-tw-keyboard-shortcut]\\\")` regardless of CSS visibility. Style the visible iframe via your `<<wrapClass>> iframe.tc-edit-texteditor` selector â€” the inner textarea is inside the iframe and not directly stylable from outside.\\n\\n!! Double-click-to-edit\\n\\nTemplate: `$:/plugins/rimir/theme/rr-text-view-editable`\\n\\nCompanion to `rr-text-editor`. Wraps a block-mode transclude in an `<$eventcatcher>` whose `$dblclick` sets the caller's `editState` tiddler to `\\\"yes\\\"`. Use it where the host already has an edit/view toggle so users get a discoverable gesture in addition to any toggle button.\\n\\n|!Variable (via `<$let>`) |!Description |\\n|`editState` |State tiddler the `$dblclick` action sets to `\\\"yes\\\"` |\\n|`viewTiddler` |(Optional) tiddler to render in block mode. If blank, uses the surrounding `<$tiddler>`/currentTiddler context |\\n\\n```\\n<$let editState=<<noteEditState>> viewTiddler=<<activeNote>>>\\n<$transclude $tiddler=\\\"$:/plugins/rimir/theme/rr-text-view-editable\\\" $mode=\\\"block\\\"/>\\n</$let>\\n```\\n\\nRenders as `<div class=\\\"rr-text-view-editable tc-eventcatcher\\\">â€¦</div>`. The class adds a subtle `cursor: text` hint; restyle by overriding the rule in your plugin.\\n\\n!! Utilities\\n\\n|!Class |!Purpose |\\n|`rr-muted` |Muted foreground color |\\n|`rr-mono` |Monospace font |\\n|`rr-nowrap` |No text wrapping |\\n|`rr-small` |0.85em font size |\\n\\n</$fill>\\n</$transclude>\\n\"},\"$:/plugins/rimir/theme/doc/tw-internals\":{\"title\":\"$:/plugins/rimir/theme/doc/tw-internals\",\"created\":\"20260315120000000\",\"modified\":\"20260315120000000\",\"rdt.order\":\"7\",\"rdt.plugin-key\":\"theme\",\"rdt.plugin-name\":\"theme\",\"rdt.plugin-subtitle\":\"Shared visual CSS classes for rimir plugins\",\"rdt.section\":\"TW Internals\",\"type\":\"text/vnd.tiddlywiki\",\"text\":\"<$transclude $tiddler=\\\"$:/plugins/rimir/doc-template/templates/page\\\">\\n<$fill $name=\\\"body\\\">\\n\\n!! $:/tags/Stylesheet\\n\\n`styles.tid` is tagged `$:/tags/Stylesheet`. TiddlyWiki collects all tiddlers with this tag at startup and injects their text content as `<style>` elements in the page `<head>`. The CSS is wikified first, which is what allows `<<colour ...>>` macro expansion.\\n\\n!! <<colour>> macro\\n\\nTiddlyWiki's palette system provides the `<<colour name>>` macro, which resolves to a CSS color value from the active palette tiddler (e.g., `$:/palettes/Vanilla`). The theme stylesheet uses this for borders, backgrounds, and text colors to ensure visual consistency with the user's chosen palette.\\n\\nKey palette entries used:\\n\\n|!Macro |!Typical value |!Usage in theme |\\n|`<<colour tiddler-border>>` |`#dbdbdb` |Tab borders, panel borders |\\n|`<<colour page-background>>` |`#f4f4f4` |Tab bar background |\\n|`<<colour muted-foreground>>` |`#999` |Inactive tabs, muted text |\\n|`<<colour foreground>>` |`#333` |Active tab text |\\n|`<<colour background>>` |`#fff` |Panel backgrounds |\\n|`<<colour primary>>` |`#5778d8` |Active tab border, link buttons |\\n|`<<colour alert-highlight>>` |`#ffe476` |Warning notices |\\n\\n!! $transclude with $fill\\n\\nThe callout and notice templates use `\\\\parameters` to declare their attributes, and `<$slot $name=\\\"body\\\"/>` to insert consumer-provided content. Consumers use `<$transclude $tiddler=\\\"...\\\">` with `<$fill $name=\\\"body\\\">` to inject content. This creates a transclusion boundary that enables slot/fill matching.\\n\\n!! Stylesheet loading order\\n\\nTiddlyWiki loads stylesheet tiddlers in title-alphabetical order. The theme's `styles.tid` has title `$:/plugins/rimir/theme/styles`, which sorts after TW core styles. Plugin-specific styles in other rimir plugins sort after theme due to their longer title paths, so they can safely override theme classes with equal specificity.\\n\\n</$fill>\\n</$transclude>\\n\"},\"$:/plugins/rimir/theme/documentation\":{\"title\":\"$:/plugins/rimir/theme/documentation\",\"created\":\"20260305110732195\",\"modified\":\"20260305110732195\",\"type\":\"text/vnd.tiddlywiki\",\"text\":\"<%if [[$:/plugins/rimir/doc-template]has[plugin-type]] %>\\n<$tiddler tiddler=\\\"$:/plugins/rimir/theme/doc/overview\\\">\\n<$transclude $tiddler=\\\"$:/plugins/rimir/theme/doc/overview\\\"/>\\n</$tiddler>\\n<%else%>\\nTo display this documentation, the plugin [[$:/plugins/rimir/doc-template]] needs to be installed.\\n\\nSee the [[readme|$:/plugins/rimir/theme/readme]] tab for a basic overview.\\n<%endif%>\\n\"},\"$:/plugins/rimir/theme/icon\":{\"title\":\"$:/plugins/rimir/theme/icon\",\"created\":\"20260305110732196\",\"modified\":\"20260305110732196\",\"type\":\"image/svg+xml\",\"text\":\"<svg width=\\\"22pt\\\" height=\\\"22pt\\\" xmlns=\\\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\\\" viewBox=\\\"0 0 24 24\\\" fill=\\\"none\\\" stroke=\\\"maroon\\\" stroke-width=\\\"2\\\" stroke-linecap=\\\"round\\\" stroke-linejoin=\\\"round\\\">\\n<circle cx=\\\"13.5\\\" cy=\\\"6.5\\\" r=\\\"2.5\\\"/>\\n<circle cx=\\\"17.5\\\" cy=\\\"10.5\\\" r=\\\"2.5\\\"/>\\n<circle cx=\\\"8.5\\\" cy=\\\"7.5\\\" r=\\\"2.5\\\"/>\\n<circle cx=\\\"6.5\\\" cy=\\\"12\\\" r=\\\"2.5\\\"/>\\n<path d=\\\"M12 22a7 7 0 0 0 7-7c0-2-1-4-3-6s-4-4-4-7a7 7 0 0 0-7 7c0 2 1 4 3 6s4 4 4 7z\\\"/>\\n</svg>\"},\"$:/plugins/rimir/theme/notice\":{\"title\":\"$:/plugins/rimir/theme/notice\",\"created\":\"20260305110732197\",\"modified\":\"20260305110732197\",\"type\":\"text/vnd.tiddlywiki\",\"text\":\"\\\\parameters (type:\\\"warning\\\")\\n\\n<$let noticeClass={{{ [[rr-notice rr-notice-]addsuffix<type>] }}}>\\n<div class=<<noticeClass>>>\\n<$slot $name=\\\"body\\\">\\n//No notice content.//\\n</$slot>\\n</div>\\n</$let>\\n\"},\"$:/plugins/rimir/theme/readme\":{\"title\":\"$:/plugins/rimir/theme/readme\",\"created\":\"20260305110732197\",\"modified\":\"20260305110732197\",\"type\":\"text/vnd.tiddlywiki\",\"text\":\"! theme\\n\\nShared visual CSS classes (prefix `rr-`) used across all rimir plugins. Provides consistent styling for tabs, panels, tables, callouts, notices, badges, forms, status messages, and the settings hub layout.\\n\\n!! Key features\\n\\n* ''Tabs'' â€” `rr-tabs`, `rr-tab`, `rr-tab-active` for horizontal tab bars\\n* ''Callouts'' â€” four types (info, warning, tip, danger) via reusable template\\n* ''Notices'' â€” alert banners (warning, info, danger, success)\\n* ''Badges'' â€” circular and rectangular pill badges\\n* ''Settings hub layout'' â€” sidebar + content panel classes for core-hook\\n* ''Text editor'' â€” reusable `rr-text-editor` template with EditorToolbar shortcuts (bold, italic, headings, autolist if installed) and Ctrl+Enter to leave edit mode\\n* ''Double-click-to-edit'' â€” companion `rr-text-view-editable` template wraps a view-mode transclude in an `$eventcatcher` that flips a caller-supplied `editState` to `\\\"yes\\\"` on dblclick\\n* ''Utilities'' â€” muted, mono, nowrap, small helper classes\\n\\n!! Prerequisites\\n\\nNo external prerequisites.\\n\\n!! Quick start\\n\\nInstall plugin. Use `rr-` prefixed CSS classes in your tiddlers. For callouts:\\n\\n```\\n<$transclude $tiddler=\\\"$:/plugins/rimir/theme/callout\\\" type=\\\"info\\\">\\n<$fill $name=\\\"body\\\">Your message</$fill>\\n</$transclude>\\n```\\n\\n!! Class reference\\n\\n!!! Tabs\\n\\n|!Class |!Purpose |\\n|`rr-tabs` |Flex container for tab bar |\\n|`rr-tab` |Individual tab button |\\n|`rr-tab-active` |Active tab (add alongside `rr-tab`) |\\n\\n```\\n<div class=\\\"rr-tabs\\\">\\n  <$button class=\\\"rr-tab rr-tab-active\\\">Tab 1</$button>\\n  <$button class=\\\"rr-tab\\\">Tab 2</$button>\\n</div>\\n```\\n\\n!!! Panels\\n\\n|!Class |!Purpose |\\n|`rr-panel` |Bordered container with background |\\n|`rr-panel-body` |Padded inner content area |\\n\\n!!! Tables\\n\\n|!Class |!Purpose |\\n|`rr-table` |Full-width collapsed table |\\n|`rr-row-error` |Red background row (on `<tr>`) |\\n|`rr-row-warn` |Yellow background row (on `<tr>`) |\\n\\n!!! Callouts\\n\\nUse the template `$:/plugins/rimir/theme/callout` with parameters `type` (`info`/`warning`/`tip`/`danger`) and optional `label`.\\n\\n|!Class |!Purpose |\\n|`rr-callout` |Base callout box |\\n|`rr-callout-info` |Blue left border |\\n|`rr-callout-warning` |Amber left border |\\n|`rr-callout-tip` |Green left border |\\n|`rr-callout-danger` |Red left border |\\n|`rr-callout-label` |Bold uppercase label |\\n\\n!!! Notices\\n\\nUse the template `$:/plugins/rimir/theme/notice` with parameter `type` (`warning`/`info`/`danger`/`success`).\\n\\n|!Class |!Purpose |\\n|`rr-notice` |Base notice banner |\\n|`rr-notice-warning` |Yellow background |\\n|`rr-notice-info` |Light blue background |\\n|`rr-notice-danger` |Light red background |\\n|`rr-notice-success` |Light green background |\\n\\n!!! Status Messages\\n\\n|!Class |!Purpose |\\n|`rr-status-loading` |Muted italic loading text |\\n|`rr-status-error` |Red alert box |\\n|`rr-status-success` |Green success box |\\n|`rr-status-info` |Muted info text |\\n\\n!!! Badges\\n\\n|!Class |!Purpose |\\n|`rr-badge-circle` |16px round badge |\\n|`rr-badge-added` |Green circle (use with `rr-badge-circle`) |\\n|`rr-badge-removed` |Red circle (use with `rr-badge-circle`) |\\n|`rr-badge-rect` |Rectangular pill badge |\\n\\n!!! Forms\\n\\n|!Class |!Purpose |\\n|`rr-input-row` |Flex row with gap |\\n|`rr-input` |Styled text input |\\n\\n!!! Link Buttons\\n\\n|!Class |!Purpose |\\n|`rr-link-btn` |Primary-colored link-style button |\\n|`rr-link-btn-danger` |Alert-colored variant (add alongside `rr-link-btn`) |\\n\\n!!! Settings Hub\\n\\n|!Class |!Purpose |\\n|`rr-settings-hub` |Flex container for sidebar + content layout |\\n|`rr-settings-sidebar` |Left sidebar with plugin list |\\n|`rr-settings-plugin-item` |Sidebar button for each plugin |\\n|`rr-settings-plugin-active` |Active state highlight (accent border) |\\n|`rr-settings-plugin-name` |Plugin name text (truncated) |\\n|`rr-settings-plugin-version` |Version badge |\\n|`rr-settings-content` |Right content area |\\n|`rr-settings-header` |Plugin header with icon + name + description |\\n|`rr-settings-header-name` |Plugin name in header |\\n|`rr-settings-header-desc` |Plugin description in header |\\n|`rr-settings-info-card` |Dashed info card for plugins without settings |\\n\\n!!! Text Editor\\n\\nUse the template `$:/plugins/rimir/theme/rr-text-editor` for an `<$edit-text>`-based body editor that picks up the standard EditorToolbar keyboard shortcuts (bold, italic, headings, autolist if the `sq/editor-autolist` plugin is installed) and binds Ctrl+Enter to clear an edit-state tiddler.\\n\\nCaller passes parameters via `<$let>`:\\n\\n|!Variable |!Purpose |\\n|`editTiddler` |Title of the tiddler whose `text` field is being edited |\\n|`editState` |State tiddler that gates edit mode (cleared on Ctrl+Enter) |\\n|`wrapClass` |CSS class for the outer wrapper div (controls width, height, etc.) |\\n\\n```\\n<$let editTiddler=<<myNote>> editState=\\\"$:/state/my-edit\\\" wrapClass=\\\"my-editor\\\">\\n<$transclude $tiddler=\\\"$:/plugins/rimir/theme/rr-text-editor\\\"/>\\n</$let>\\n```\\n\\nInternally renders toolbar children inside `<$edit-text>` so TW's framed editor engine binds shortcuts; the toolbar itself is hidden via `.rr-text-editor-host > .tc-editor-toolbar { display: none }`. Style the visible iframe via `<<wrapClass>> iframe.tc-edit-texteditor`.\\n\\n!!! Double-click-to-edit\\n\\nCompanion template `$:/plugins/rimir/theme/rr-text-view-editable` wraps a block-mode transclude in an `<$eventcatcher>` that sets a caller-supplied `editState` tiddler to `\\\"yes\\\"` on double-click â€” pairs with `rr-text-editor` so the same `editState` flips both directions (dblclick â†’ enter, Ctrl+Enter â†’ leave).\\n\\n|!Variable |!Purpose |\\n|`editState` |State tiddler set to `\\\"yes\\\"` on dblclick |\\n|`viewTiddler` |(Optional) tiddler to transclude. If unset, uses surrounding `<$tiddler>`/currentTiddler context |\\n\\n```\\n<$let editState=<<myEditState>> viewTiddler=<<myNote>>>\\n<$transclude $tiddler=\\\"$:/plugins/rimir/theme/rr-text-view-editable\\\" $mode=\\\"block\\\"/>\\n</$let>\\n```\\n\\nAdds class `rr-text-view-editable` (with `cursor: text`) to the wrapper div.\\n\\n!!! Utilities\\n\\n|!Class |!Purpose |\\n|`rr-muted` |Muted foreground color |\\n|`rr-mono` |Monospace font |\\n|`rr-nowrap` |No text wrapping |\\n|`rr-small` |0.85em font size |\\n\"},\"$:/plugins/rimir/theme/rr-text-editor/leave-edit\":{\"title\":\"$:/plugins/rimir/theme/rr-text-editor/leave-edit\",\"created\":\"20260429120000000\",\"modified\":\"20260429120000000\",\"tags\":\"$:/tags/EditorToolbar\",\"type\":\"text/vnd.tiddlywiki\",\"button-classes\":\"rr-text-editor-btn-hidden\",\"condition\":\"[<editState>!is[blank]]\",\"shortcuts\":\"ctrl+Enter\",\"caption\":\"Leave edit mode\",\"description\":\"Leave edit mode\",\"icon\":\"$:/core/images/done-button\",\"text\":\"<$action-setfield $tiddler=<<editState>> text=\\\"\\\"/>\\n\"},\"$:/plugins/rimir/theme/rr-text-editor\":{\"title\":\"$:/plugins/rimir/theme/rr-text-editor\",\"created\":\"20260429120000000\",\"modified\":\"20260429120000000\",\"type\":\"text/vnd.tiddlywiki\",\"text\":\"\\\\whitespace trim\\n\\n<!-- Caller passes editTiddler, editState, wrapClass via <$let> -->\\n<div class=<<wrapClass>>>\\n<div class=\\\"rr-text-editor-host\\\">\\n<$edit-text tiddler=<<editTiddler>> field=\\\"text\\\" class=\\\"tc-edit-texteditor\\\">\\n<$set name=\\\"targetTiddler\\\" value=<<editTiddler>>>\\n<$list filter=\\\"[all[shadows+tiddlers]tag[$:/tags/EditorToolbar]!has[draft.of]]\\\">\\n<$transclude tiddler=\\\"$:/core/ui/EditTemplate/body/toolbar/button\\\" mode=\\\"inline\\\"/>\\n</$list>\\n</$set>\\n</$edit-text>\\n</div>\\n</div>\\n\"},\"$:/plugins/rimir/theme/rr-text-view-editable\":{\"title\":\"$:/plugins/rimir/theme/rr-text-view-editable\",\"created\":\"20260430101717000\",\"modified\":\"20260430101717000\",\"type\":\"text/vnd.tiddlywiki\",\"text\":\"\\\\whitespace trim\\n\\n<!-- Caller passes editState via <$let> (required) and optionally viewTiddler.\\n     When viewTiddler is set, that tiddler is transcluded; otherwise the\\n     surrounding <$tiddler>/currentTiddler context is used.\\n     Double-clicking sets editState to \\\"yes\\\" so the host can render rr-text-editor. -->\\n<$eventcatcher tag=\\\"div\\\" class=\\\"rr-text-view-editable\\\" $dblclick=\\\"\\\"\\\"<$action-setfield $tiddler=<<editState>> text=\\\"yes\\\"/>\\\"\\\"\\\">\\n<%if [<viewTiddler>!is[blank]] %>\\n<$transclude $tiddler=<<viewTiddler>> $mode=\\\"block\\\"/>\\n<%else%>\\n<$transclude $mode=\\\"block\\\"/>\\n<%endif%>\\n</$eventcatcher>\\n\"},\"$:/plugins/rimir/theme/settings\":{\"title\":\"$:/plugins/rimir/theme/settings\",\"created\":\"20260305110732198\",\"modified\":\"20260305110732198\",\"type\":\"text/vnd.tiddlywiki\",\"text\":\"<div class=\\\"rr-settings-info-card\\\">\\nNo configurable settings. Future settings will appear here.\\n</div>\\n\"},\"$:/plugins/rimir/theme/styles\":{\"title\":\"$:/plugins/rimir/theme/styles\",\"created\":\"20260305110732198\",\"modified\":\"20260305110732198\",\"tags\":\"$:/tags/Stylesheet\",\"type\":\"text/vnd.tiddlywiki\",\"text\":\"/* ============================================================\\n   rimir Theme â€” Shared Visual Classes\\n   Prefix: rr-\\n   ============================================================ */\\n\\n/* --- Tabs --- */\\n.rr-tabs {\\n\\tdisplay: flex;\\n\\tborder-bottom: 1px solid <<colour tiddler-border>>;\\n\\tbackground: <<colour page-background>>;\\n\\tborder-radius: 4px 4px 0 0;\\n}\\n\\n.rr-tab {\\n\\tpadding: 6px 16px;\\n\\tborder: none;\\n\\tbackground: none;\\n\\tcursor: pointer;\\n\\tcolor: <<colour muted-foreground>>;\\n\\tborder-bottom: 2px solid transparent;\\n\\tfont-size: 0.9em;\\n\\tfont-family: inherit;\\n\\tline-height: inherit;\\n}\\n\\n.rr-tab:hover {\\n\\tcolor: <<colour foreground>>;\\n\\tbackground: <<colour tiddler-background>>;\\n}\\n\\n.rr-tab-active {\\n\\tcolor: <<colour foreground>>;\\n\\tborder-bottom-color: <<colour primary>>;\\n\\tfont-weight: bold;\\n}\\n\\n/* --- Panels --- */\\n.rr-panel {\\n\\tborder: 1px solid <<colour tiddler-border>>;\\n\\tborder-radius: 4px;\\n\\tbackground: <<colour tiddler-background>>;\\n}\\n\\n.rr-panel-body {\\n\\tpadding: 8px 12px;\\n}\\n\\n/* --- Tables --- */\\n.rr-table {\\n\\twidth: 100%;\\n\\tborder-collapse: collapse;\\n\\tfont-size: 0.9em;\\n}\\n\\n.rr-table th,\\n.rr-table td {\\n\\tborder: 1px solid <<colour table-border>>;\\n\\tpadding: 4px 8px;\\n\\ttext-align: left;\\n}\\n\\n.rr-table th {\\n\\tbackground: <<colour table-header-background>>;\\n\\tcolor: <<colour muted-foreground>>;\\n\\tfont-weight: normal;\\n}\\n\\n.rr-table tr:hover td {\\n\\tfilter: brightness(0.95);\\n}\\n\\n.rr-row-error td {\\n\\tbackground: #fdd;\\n}\\n\\n.rr-row-warn td {\\n\\tbackground: #fed;\\n}\\n\\n.rr-row-error td:first-child,\\n.rr-row-warn td:first-child {\\n\\twhite-space: nowrap;\\n}\\n\\n/* --- Callout boxes --- */\\n.rr-callout {\\n\\tpadding: 12px 16px;\\n\\tborder-radius: 4px;\\n\\tmargin: 1em 0;\\n\\tborder-left: 4px solid;\\n\\tfont-size: 0.92em;\\n}\\n\\n.rr-callout-label {\\n\\tfont-weight: 700;\\n\\ttext-transform: uppercase;\\n\\tfont-size: 0.8em;\\n\\tletter-spacing: 0.5px;\\n\\tmargin-bottom: 4px;\\n}\\n\\n.rr-callout-info {\\n\\tborder-left-color: #3b82f6;\\n\\tbackground: rgba(59, 130, 246, 0.08);\\n}\\n.rr-callout-info .rr-callout-label { color: #3b82f6; }\\n\\n.rr-callout-warning {\\n\\tborder-left-color: #d97706;\\n\\tbackground: rgba(217, 119, 6, 0.08);\\n}\\n.rr-callout-warning .rr-callout-label { color: #d97706; }\\n\\n.rr-callout-tip {\\n\\tborder-left-color: #16a34a;\\n\\tbackground: rgba(22, 163, 74, 0.08);\\n}\\n.rr-callout-tip .rr-callout-label { color: #16a34a; }\\n\\n.rr-callout-danger {\\n\\tborder-left-color: #dc2626;\\n\\tbackground: rgba(220, 38, 38, 0.08);\\n}\\n.rr-callout-danger .rr-callout-label { color: #dc2626; }\\n\\n/* --- Notices (full-width banners) --- */\\n.rr-notice {\\n\\tmargin-top: 12px;\\n\\tpadding: 12px;\\n\\tborder-radius: 4px;\\n\\tfont-weight: bold;\\n}\\n\\n.rr-notice-warning {\\n\\tbackground: #fff3cd;\\n\\tborder: 1px solid #ffc107;\\n}\\n\\n.rr-notice-info {\\n\\tbackground: #d1ecf1;\\n\\tborder: 1px solid #bee5eb;\\n}\\n\\n.rr-notice-danger {\\n\\tbackground: #f8d7da;\\n\\tborder: 1px solid #f5c6cb;\\n}\\n\\n.rr-notice-success {\\n\\tbackground: #d4edda;\\n\\tborder: 1px solid #c3e6cb;\\n}\\n\\n/* --- Status messages --- */\\n.rr-status-loading {\\n\\tcolor: <<colour muted-foreground>>;\\n\\tfont-style: italic;\\n\\tpadding: 8px 0;\\n}\\n\\n.rr-status-error {\\n\\tcolor: <<colour alert-highlight>>;\\n\\tpadding: 8px;\\n\\tbackground: <<colour alert-background>>;\\n\\tborder: 1px solid <<colour alert-border>>;\\n\\tborder-radius: 3px;\\n\\tfont-size: 0.9em;\\n}\\n\\n.rr-status-success {\\n\\tcolor: <<colour foreground>>;\\n\\tpadding: 8px;\\n\\tbackground: #d4edda;\\n\\tborder: 1px solid #c3e6cb;\\n\\tborder-radius: 3px;\\n\\tfont-size: 0.9em;\\n}\\n\\n.rr-status-info {\\n\\tcolor: <<colour muted-foreground>>;\\n\\tpadding: 8px 0;\\n}\\n\\n/* --- Badges --- */\\n.rr-badge-circle {\\n\\tdisplay: inline-block;\\n\\twidth: 16px;\\n\\theight: 16px;\\n\\tline-height: 16px;\\n\\ttext-align: center;\\n\\tborder-radius: 50%;\\n\\tfont-size: 12px;\\n\\tfont-weight: bold;\\n\\tmargin-right: 4px;\\n\\tvertical-align: middle;\\n}\\n\\n.rr-badge-added {\\n\\tbackground: #28a745;\\n\\tcolor: white;\\n}\\n\\n.rr-badge-removed {\\n\\tbackground: #dc3545;\\n\\tcolor: white;\\n}\\n\\n.rr-badge-rect {\\n\\tdisplay: inline-block;\\n\\tfont-size: 0.75em;\\n\\tfont-weight: 600;\\n\\tpadding: 2px 8px;\\n\\tborder-radius: 4px;\\n\\ttext-transform: uppercase;\\n\\tletter-spacing: 0.5px;\\n}\\n\\n/* --- Forms --- */\\n.rr-input-row {\\n\\tdisplay: flex;\\n\\tgap: 8px;\\n\\tmargin-bottom: 8px;\\n}\\n\\n.rr-input {\\n\\tflex: 1;\\n\\tpadding: 4px 8px;\\n\\tborder: 1px solid <<colour code-border>>;\\n\\tborder-radius: 3px;\\n\\tfont-size: 0.9em;\\n\\tbackground: <<colour code-background>>;\\n}\\n\\n/* --- Link buttons --- */\\n.rr-link-btn {\\n\\tcolor: <<colour primary>>;\\n\\tfont-size: 0.85em;\\n\\tmargin-right: 8px;\\n}\\n\\n.rr-link-btn:hover {\\n\\ttext-decoration: underline;\\n}\\n\\n.rr-link-btn-danger {\\n\\tcolor: <<colour alert-highlight>>;\\n\\tmargin-right: 0;\\n}\\n\\n/* --- Utilities --- */\\n.rr-muted {\\n\\tcolor: <<colour muted-foreground>>;\\n}\\n\\n.rr-mono {\\n\\tfont-family: monospace;\\n}\\n\\n.rr-nowrap {\\n\\twhite-space: nowrap;\\n}\\n\\n.rr-small {\\n\\tfont-size: 0.85em;\\n}\\n\\n/* --- Settings Hub (ControlPanel vertical tabs) --- */\\n.rr-settings-hub {\\n\\tdisplay: flex;\\n\\tgap: 0;\\n\\tmin-height: 400px;\\n\\tborder: 1px solid <<colour tiddler-border>>;\\n\\tborder-radius: 6px;\\n\\toverflow: hidden;\\n\\tbackground: <<colour tiddler-background>>;\\n}\\n\\n.rr-settings-sidebar {\\n\\twidth: 220px;\\n\\tmin-width: 220px;\\n\\tbackground: <<colour page-background>>;\\n\\tborder-right: 1px solid <<colour tiddler-border>>;\\n\\tpadding: 8px 0;\\n\\toverflow-y: auto;\\n}\\n\\n.rr-settings-plugin-item {\\n\\tdisplay: flex;\\n\\talign-items: center;\\n\\tgap: 8px;\\n\\twidth: 100%;\\n\\tpadding: 8px 14px;\\n\\tborder: none;\\n\\tbackground: none;\\n\\tcursor: pointer;\\n\\ttext-align: left;\\n\\tfont-family: inherit;\\n\\tfont-size: 0.9em;\\n\\tcolor: <<colour foreground>>;\\n\\tborder-left: 3px solid transparent;\\n\\ttransition: background 0.15s;\\n}\\n\\n.rr-settings-plugin-item:hover {\\n\\tbackground: <<colour tiddler-background>>;\\n}\\n\\n.rr-settings-plugin-active {\\n\\tbackground: <<colour tiddler-background>>;\\n\\tborder-left-color: <<colour primary>>;\\n\\tfont-weight: 600;\\n}\\n\\n.rr-settings-plugin-name {\\n\\tflex: 1;\\n\\toverflow: hidden;\\n\\ttext-overflow: ellipsis;\\n\\twhite-space: nowrap;\\n}\\n\\n.rr-settings-plugin-version {\\n\\tfont-size: 0.8em;\\n\\twhite-space: nowrap;\\n}\\n\\n.rr-settings-content {\\n\\tflex: 1;\\n\\tpadding: 20px 24px;\\n\\toverflow-y: auto;\\n}\\n\\n.rr-settings-header {\\n\\tdisplay: flex;\\n\\talign-items: center;\\n\\tgap: 12px;\\n\\tmargin-bottom: 20px;\\n\\tpadding-bottom: 12px;\\n\\tborder-bottom: 1px solid <<colour tiddler-border>>;\\n}\\n\\n.rr-settings-header-name {\\n\\tfont-size: 1.2em;\\n\\tfont-weight: 600;\\n}\\n\\n.rr-settings-header-desc {\\n\\tfont-size: 0.9em;\\n\\tmargin-top: 2px;\\n}\\n\\n.rr-settings-info-card {\\n\\tpadding: 16px;\\n\\tborder: 1px dashed <<colour tiddler-border>>;\\n\\tborder-radius: 6px;\\n\\ttext-align: center;\\n\\tcolor: <<colour muted-foreground>>;\\n}\\n\\n/* --- Shared rich-text editor (rr-text-editor) ---\\n   Toolbar children are rendered inside <$edit-text> only to bind\\n   keyboard shortcuts (autolist Enter/Tab/shift-Tab + Ctrl+Enter to\\n   leave edit mode). The toolbar itself stays hidden â€” shortcuts still\\n   fire because querySelectorAll finds the elements regardless. */\\n.rr-text-editor-host > .tc-editor-toolbar {\\n\\tdisplay: none;\\n}\\n.rr-text-editor-btn-hidden {\\n\\tdisplay: none;\\n}\\n\\n/* --- Double-click-to-edit view wrapper (rr-text-view-editable) --- */\\n.rr-text-view-editable {\\n\\tcursor: text;\\n}\\n\"},\"$:/plugins/rimir/theme/test/test-callout\":{\"title\":\"$:/plugins/rimir/theme/test/test-callout\",\"description\":\"Test callout procedure renders correct structure with type and label\",\"type\":\"text/vnd.tiddlywiki-multiple\",\"tags\":\"[[$:/tags/wiki-test-spec]]\",\"text\":\"title: Output\\n\\n\\\\whitespace trim\\n\\\\procedure callout(type:\\\"info\\\", label:\\\"\\\")\\n\\\\whitespace trim\\n<$let\\n  calloutClass={{{ [[rr-callout rr-callout-]addsuffix<type>] }}}\\n  resolvedLabel={{{ [<label>!is[blank]] :else[<type>uppercase[]] }}}\\n>\\n<div class=<<calloutClass>>>\\n<div class=\\\"rr-callout-label\\\"><$text text=<<resolvedLabel>>/></div>\\n<$slot $name=\\\"body\\\">\\nDefault content\\n</$slot>\\n</div>\\n</$let>\\n\\\\end\\n\\n<$transclude $variable=\\\"callout\\\" type=\\\"warn\\\" label=\\\"Watch out\\\">\\n<$fill $name=\\\"body\\\">\\nHello\\n</$fill>\\n</$transclude>\\n<$transclude $variable=\\\"callout\\\" type=\\\"info\\\">\\n<$fill $name=\\\"body\\\">\\nInfo text\\n</$fill>\\n</$transclude>\\n+\\ntitle: ExpectedResult\\n\\n<p><div class=\\\"rr-callout rr-callout-warn\\\"><div class=\\\"rr-callout-label\\\">Watch out</div>Hello</div><div class=\\\"rr-callout rr-callout-info\\\"><div class=\\\"rr-callout-label\\\">INFO</div>Info text</div></p>\\n+\\ntitle: Narrative\\n\\nVerifies callout procedure renders div structure with correct CSS classes for type and label.\\n\"},\"$:/plugins/rimir/theme/test/test-notice\":{\"title\":\"$:/plugins/rimir/theme/test/test-notice\",\"description\":\"Test notice procedure renders correct structure with type parameter\",\"type\":\"text/vnd.tiddlywiki-multiple\",\"tags\":\"[[$:/tags/wiki-test-spec]]\",\"text\":\"title: Output\\n\\n\\\\whitespace trim\\n\\\\procedure notice(type:\\\"warning\\\")\\n\\\\whitespace trim\\n<$let noticeClass={{{ [[rr-notice rr-notice-]addsuffix<type>] }}}>\\n<div class=<<noticeClass>>>\\n<$slot $name=\\\"body\\\">\\nDefault notice\\n</$slot>\\n</div>\\n</$let>\\n\\\\end\\n\\n<$transclude $variable=\\\"notice\\\" type=\\\"error\\\">\\n<$fill $name=\\\"body\\\">\\nError occurred\\n</$fill>\\n</$transclude>\\n<$transclude $variable=\\\"notice\\\">\\n<$fill $name=\\\"body\\\">\\nDefault type\\n</$fill>\\n</$transclude>\\n+\\ntitle: ExpectedResult\\n\\n<p><div class=\\\"rr-notice rr-notice-error\\\">Error occurred</div><div class=\\\"rr-notice rr-notice-warning\\\">Default type</div></p>\\n+\\ntitle: Narrative\\n\\nVerifies notice procedure renders div structure with correct CSS classes for type parameter.\\n\"},\"/home/runner/work/tw-plugin-library/tw-plugin-library/wiki/plugins/rimir/theme/test-edition/tiddlywiki.info\":{\"title\":\"/home/runner/work/tw-plugin-library/tw-plugin-library/wiki/plugins/rimir/theme/test-edition/tiddlywiki.info\",\"text\":\"{\\n    \\\"description\\\": \\\"Test edition for theme\\\",\\n    \\\"plugins\\\": [\\n        \\\"tiddlywiki/jasmine\\\",\\n        \\\"rimir/theme\\\"\\n    ],\\n    \\\"themes\\\": [\\n        \\\"tiddlywiki/vanilla\\\",\\n        \\\"tiddlywiki/snowwhite\\\"\\n    ]\\n}\\n\",\"type\":\".info\"}}}"}